ai-ezio
=======

ai-ezio is a downstream, hax-derived workflow-native coding agent for the
ai-creed / ai-whisper ecosystem.

Lineage
-------

ai-ezio is derived from hax, a minimalist terminal coding assistant in C,
originally authored by Oleksandr Chekhovskyi.

  Upstream:  hax        https://github.com/OleksandrChekhovskyi/hax
  Base:      commit 8fd139b5db49bd0b1d552c2530a18b547b3f4f4c (2026-05-29)

ai-ezio retains hax's core provider / tool / streaming architecture (vendored
as a git submodule under `vendor/hax`) and adds:

  - a machine-readable JSONL protocol emitted from hax via a small C patch;
  - a TypeScript harness for mounted / machine-controlled sessions;
  - an ai-whisper adapter for workflow handoffs and handbacks;
  - first-class skills discoverability UX.

